# docs/steve-handoff/ is an UNTRACKED scratch tree (Steve demo handoff).
# It carries credential-SHAPED references (Clerk app/instance/user ids, the
# demo access code, CLERK_SECRET_KEY *names* and sk_test_… prose placeholders)
# and ~4MB of captured HTML. None of it is a real secret VALUE (verified
# 2026-06-01: the only key-shaped string is the public Clerk pk_test_
# publishable key, which is also in .env.example), but a careless
# `git add docs/` must not be able to publish any of it.
#
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING in this directory by default, then explicitly
# allow-list only files that are safe + intended to be tracked. To deliberately
# track a curated handoff doc later, add a `!path` line below (and confirm it
# carries no real secret value first).

# Ignore-all default for this scratch tree.
*

# Allow the ignore policy itself to be reviewable.
!.gitignore

# NOTE: nothing else is allow-listed yet. The large captures
# (steve-desktop.html, steve-mobile.html), the audit/ screenshots+crops+tmp,
# *.log, and every credential-shaped markdown (DEMO-HANDOFF.md, demo-design/*)
# stay untracked until a specific file is curated and added with `!<path>`.
